title: atlantic_mackerel
body:
A species of mackerel. Sold in Japan as [i]Taiseiyou saba[/i] (literal translation from English), Norwegian mackerel ([i]Norway saba[/i]),  or simply mackerel ([i]saba[/i], a general term for [i]Scomber[/i], [i]Rastrelliger[/i] and [i]Grammatorcynus[/i]). Also known as Boston mackerel or Scottish mackerel.

"The Atlantic mackerel's body is elongate, steel-blue marked with wavy black lines dorsally and silvery-white ventrally, its snout long and pointed. It possesses two spiny dorsal fins, which are spaced far apart, two pectoral fins, and small caudal and anal fins, also spaced far apart." [1]

h4. See also

* [[Fish]]
* Not to be confused with the [[okhotsk atka mackerel]].

h4. Links

* [1] "Wikipedia entry":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_mackerel

title: gourd
body:
The gourd is a member of the plant family Cucurbitaceae and a relative of the [[pumpkin]]. When dried, its fruit can be hollowed out and used as a container. It is also used as food.

Most commonly depicted on Danbooru is the dumbbell-shaped fruit of the bottle gourd, or calabash, which can be used to hold liquids like [[sake]].

h4.See also

* [[Tag Group:Food Tags]]

title: maou_(maoyuu)
body:
"Demon Queen"

The female lead protagonist. The 43rd ruler of the Demon World and the youngest to rule by demon standards, she is a powerful sorceress but has no experience in battle. Wise and smart, her vast knowledge comes from the "Exterior Library", a hidden dimension where knowledge of the past and future is kept and where her clan lived. Despite her knowledge, she is considered incompetent by the warmongering demon clans. Seeing what would happen to the war if it didn't end without the problems that it cause fixed, she awaited the arrival of the [[yuusha_(maoyuu)|Hero]] so she could ask for his help to end war the right way. After finally getting him as her ally, she and the Hero travel to the Human world where she takes the identity of the "Crimson Scholar", a human noble who has come to help the lower classes.

See also:

* [[Maoyuu Maou Yuusha]]
* [[maid-chou_(maoyuu)|Maid-Chou]]
* [[Maou Beluzel]]
* [[huge_breasts|Useless meat]]

title: onna_mahoutsukai_(maoyuu)
body:
Female Magician.
A supporting character in [[Maoyuu Maou Yuusha]], she was a part of the [[yuusha (maoyuu)|Hero's]] team.

title: yuusha_(maoyuu)
body:
"Hero"

The male lead protagonist. A young and powerful human warrior, he came to the Demon World to end the evil of the demons by killing their leader, the [[maou_(maoyuu)|Demon Queen]]. Instead, he learns the harsh reality the Human/Demon war was never a battle between Good and Evil but a period of turmoil where both weak, innocent humans and demons are oppressed and taken advantage by the corrupt and powerful from both sides. Wishing to end the war the right way with the least repercussions, he agrees to become the Demon Queen's ally in her plans to stop the war.

See also:

* [[Maoyuu Maou Yuusha]]
* [[Yuusha Masatoshi]]

body:

[i]Ishtar[/i] is the Mesopotamian goddess of love, beauty, sex, desire, fertility, war, combat, and political power.

title: chiliarch_(elsword)
body:
One of [[luciela r. sourcream|Lu]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[timoria (elsword)|Timoria]]. She wears her hair in [[twintails]], has large blue horns, and she has a black [[crown]] over her blue [[animal hood]] [[coat]]. She keeps her coat together with a [[brooch]], and also wears her large claw on her right hand, blue shorts, a striped blue thighhigh on her right leg, a striped blue kneehigh on her left leg, and spiked shoes.

[i]Chiliarch[/i] is a military rank derived from the Greek word [i]chiliarchos[/i], meaning [i]Commander of a Thousand[/i].

title: lancia_delta_s4
body:
Lancia's Delta S4 was a rally car developed for the WRC's short-lived Group B category, where the cars had a massive power output compared to their Group A counterparts. Like all Group B rally cara it had a civilian version called the Delta S4 Stradale.

It had an Abarth tuned 1,759 cc inline-4 engine, which produced 550 horsepower; made possible by the use of a turbocharger and supercharger; a system called twin-charging.

The S4 made it's debut at the 1985 event of the RAC Rally (now called the Wales Rally GB) and won that event; at the hands of up-and-coming Finnish rally driver Henri Toivonen; who also won the Monte Carlo Rally of 1986.

Sadly however, with so much unfulfilled potential left, Toivonen and his co-driver Sergio Cresto; both died in the 1986 Tour de Corse, when their S4 Delta missed a tight left-hand hairpin and plunged off into a wooded ravine and exploded in flames; leaving only the badly burnt spaceframe and chassis. The crash was nearly a year after Lancia's Attilio Bettega died after crashing his Lancia 037 (the car that was replaced by the S4.)

A comment made by Cesare Fiorio, then team boss of the Lancia rally team, just told of how much unfulfilled potential Henri Toivonen still had to show; as he was the only driver on the team who could control Lancia's S4 Delta but Toivonen himself said that the car had a mind of it's own and that he himself didn't know how to drive it.

title: fal_l1a1_(upotte!!)
body:
Upotte's portrayal of the L1A1 Self-Loading Rifle (referred to as the FAL L1A1 in Upotte!!).

FAL, called "Farru" is tall, brown haired, modestly confident (perhaps cocky) and wears a tan blazer and long, shin length skirt. She acts as the big sister to the protagonist FNC ("Funco") and is acquaintances and classmates with M14 and G3 ("jiisuri"). M14, G3 and FAL are all members of the "big three" battle rifles, 7.62 NATO chambered weapons used as their host country's main service rifle and exported to other places. FAL is proud of her position among these rifles and many of her mannerisms reflect this.

title: rune_slayer_(elsword)
body: One of [[elsword (character)|Elsword]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[rune master (elsword)|Rune Master]]. His [[spiked_hair|hair is spiky]] and tied into two small ponytails, and he wears a black [[halterneck]], black [[fingerless gloves]], a red [[belt]], black pants with white chaps, and shoes.

title: fatal_phantom_(elsword)

title: deadly_chaser_(elsword)
body: One of [[chung_seiker|Chung]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[fatal phantom (elsword)|Fatal Phantom]]. His hair is short and spiky. His [[full armor|full-body armor]] Freiturnier has a blue scarf with a red underside, two blue belt buckles extending from his shoulders, white armor with a black patch on the chest, and white [[greaves]] covering his legs. The biggest difference between this class and [[shooting guardian (elsword)|Shooting Guardian]] is that Chung wields two Silver Shooter pistols instead of one. In berserk mode, his helmet has no blue hair; instead it has a 'hood' that surrounds his cranium while a mask covers his face.

title: noblesse_(elsword)
body: One of [[luciela r. sourcream|Lu]]'s character classes, succeeded by [[ishtar (elsword)|Ishtar]]. She has very long hair tied into [[twintails]] that have rings at the bottom of each one, and she has a black crown and blue [[horns]] on her head. She wears a white [[leotard]], [[detached sleeves]], a [[blue bow]], has blue [[bat wings]] and a demon tail, a chain, and blue thigh-length [[greaves]].

title: chevalier_(elsword)

[[ciel (elsword)|Ciel]]'s character class following [[royal guard (elsword)|Royal Guard]], and accompanies [[Luciela R. Sourcream]]'s [[ishtar (elsword)|Ishtar]].

[i]Chevalier[/i] is a crusader who will commit any act in the name of their god, and the term means [i][[knight]][/i] in French.

title: royal_guard_(elsword)

His outfit makes him resemble a [[butler]] since he is [[luciela r. sourcream|Lu]]'s servant. It consists of a black jacket, [[white bow]], [[black gloves]], a blue vest, black pants and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

title: saigusa_haruka
body:
A Character from [[little_busters!|Little Busters!]]. Haruka is a schoolmate of Riki's from a different class, but despite this, always seems to find time to hang around in Riki's classroom. She is a problem child and will start an uproar for her own personal enjoyment, which causes her twin sister, the public morals chairman Kanata Futaki, to often chase after her. She use marbles as a weapon to distract the public morals committee from chasing her, and when Riki is with her, she will drag Riki away, explaining that being captured by the public morals committee means big trouble for her. [spoiler]The truth is, she was abused by her family (not her parents, who were kept away from her and Kanata), while Kanata was seemingly treated very well, though truthfully she was not. She thus starts trouble to bother her sister and shame her family name.[/spoiler] She works part-time in the school's cafeteria to get permission to use the oven to bake muffins and cakes. 

Looks the same as [[Futaki Kanata]]. Tell them apart by:

Kanata: usually no thighhighs, golden eyes
Haruka: often black/white striped thighhighs, blue eyes

title: hair_behind_eyewear
body:
For when eyewear is being worn in their normal position, but with the eyewear being over the top of hair (usually [[bangs]]) rather than the more normal style of having hair over the eyewear.

This often in combination with [[hair over one eye]] or [[hair over eyes]].

Note that this tag should not be used if the eyewear is not being worn in the normal position over the character's eyes, nor if the eyewear is obscured by the hair in a way that suggests it to be visible through the hair rather than actually on top of it.

The following are some examples of the tag:
post #2501543
post #2520277
post #2962784

The following are not examples of this tag:
post #2616875 - the eyewear is not actually being worn.
post #2717327 - the hair looks to be over the eyewear, which is merely visible beneath it.
post #2945525 - the eyewear with hair behind is not in the normal position.

title: sonderkommando_elbe
body:
Named "Special Command Elbe" after the river where it's headquarters was near to; this special unit of the Luftwaffe employed the exact opposite of the earlier Sturmböcke units; by using stripped down Messerschmitt Bf-109G fighters (excess armor and armament except a single MG131) for use as ramming USAAF heavy bombers.

The unit only saw one combat mission on 7th of April, 1945 with a sortie by 180 pilots, but recorded only 15 US bombers destroyed and 8 of their own planes lost. 

Unlike the kamikaze units of the Japanese; Elbe pilots only had a lightly armored Bf-109G plus a 13mm machine gun with only 60 bullets (only a few Elbe pilots used this to successfully down US bombers) , but used the propeller of their aircraft to physically damage US bombers.

title: sturmbock_(unit)
body:
When USAAF heavy bombers started appearing they caused problems for the Luftwaffe's fighter force, whose armaments at the time could not adequately destroy B-17s and B-24s deployed in the combat box formation. And fighter escort usage meant the earlier solution using Bf110 bomber destroyers was no longer viable.

So the decision was made to modify the rugged Focke Wulf 190 into a bomber interceptor, modifying it with heavier armaments including 30mm cannons and unguided rockets plus heavy armor; but these rendered the planes cumbersome and useless without fighter escort.

title: hms_lion_(1939)
body:
Lead ship of her class, which were planned but cancelled in early WWII. With this class the UK finally discarded all treaty restrictions. Originally planned as enlarged 16in gun version of the King George V the class went through many iterations, the last of which were planned during the late 1940s.

This is the entry about the unbuilt British battleship, for the [[HMS Lion (1910)|battlecruiser that was actually constructed pre-WWI]]... well danbooru doesn't actually have a page for her yet.

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia: Lion-class battleship":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion-class_battleship]

h4.See also

* [[List of Ships]]

title: sentinel_(x-men)
body:
An [[X-Men]] type of villain that is well known for its appearance in the [[Marvel vs. Capcom]] series.

In the [[Marvel]] universe the [b]Sentinel[/b] is a type of [[giant]] humanoid sentient [[robot]] or [[mecha]] designed for hunting down super-powered mutants.

They are very powerful and have energy weapons built on their hands as well as telescopic robotic tentacles designed to capture their prey. The Sentinels are usually deployed in vast numbers.

There is a [[meme]] involving Sentinel's orange and blue palette in [[Marvel vs. Capcom 3]] called "Mango Sentinel", due to how its armor resembles the color of [[mango]] flesh.
[quote]IFC Yipes said:
Oh he got da "Mango Sentinal!":http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sZZUMjoxfZA Yoithink of NEW YOHK KNICKS!
[/quote]

body:
Subsonic [[fighter jet]], successor to the [[MiG-15]], thousands produced. Exported to a number of nations and served in numerous conflicts, the most famous of them Vietnam War and various Arab-Israeli conflicts.

title: mig-19
body:
First [[Soviet]] supersonic [[fighter jet]], moderately successful on the export market. Licensed produced in PRC as the J-6. Fought in the Six Day War as well as a number of other conflicts. Later variants armed with beam rider missiles.


h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikoyan-Gurevich_MiG-19]

title: mig-23
body:
Soviet swing-wing fighter jet. Intended to be the successor of the MiG-21 it's complexity of the swing wing gear prevent it from becoming a full replacement, merely supplementing the MiG-21 instead. Exported to a number of countries. Fought in the Iraq-Iran War and the 1st Gulf War. A ground attack variant of it became the [[MiG-27]].

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikoyan-Gurevich_MiG-23]

h4.See also

* [[List of Airplanes]]

title: hms_prince_of_wales
body:
[[Battleship]] of the King George V class, took part in the battle of Denmark Strait (in which she was not finished fitting out, still having civilian contractors on board) and the subsequent hunt for Bismarck. Was later sunk along with [[HMS Repulse]] by Japanese land based aircrafts, the first capital ships to be sunk by aircrafts while at sea, underway, and at full readiness.

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Prince_of_Wales_(53)]

h4.See also

* [[List of Ships]]
other_names: プリンス・オブ・ウェールズ(戦艦)

title: hms_repulse
body:
[[Battlecruiser]] of the Renown class. Originally a R class battleship but changed to a battlecruiser before being laid down. Was upgraded between the wars but less than that of her sister, was sunk along with [[HMS Prince]] of Wales by Japanese land based aircrafts.

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Repulse_(1916)]

h4.See also

* [[List of Ships]]

title: tu-22m
body:
The replacement/successor to the [[Tu-22]], and despite its name has little in common with its predecessor. Used in the maritime strike and bombing roles in Soviet and Russian service. Sometimes mislabeled as the Tu-26.

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tupolev_Tu-22M]

h4.See also

* [[Tu-22]]
* [[List of Airplanes]]

title: b-1_lancer
body:
[[us_air_force|USAF]] [[bomber]], originally designed as a supersonic bomber to serve as the successor to the B-58 and replacement for the B-52. That version was cancelled with the Carter administration. Uncancelled by the Reagan administration, it became a subsonic bomber supplementing the B-52. Notable for its swing wing and limited stealth features.

h4.External links

* "Wikipedia article":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rockwell_B-1_Lancer]

In the time of [b]"Dark Reign"[/b] story arc famous villain [[Bullseye_(marvel)|Bullseye]] who was part of the [b]Dark Avengers[/b] have [[Hawkeye_(marvel)|Hawkeye]] as his public identity.

title: t-26
body: Soviet interwar period light [[tank]], exported to a number of countries and fought in diverse conflicts such as the Second Sino-Japan war to the Spanish Civil War.despite it's obsolescence it served throughout WWII, as late as the Soviet invasion of Manchuria of 1945.

title: t-62
body: Soviet cold war era tank. Intended as the successor of the T-55 it was of limited success due to advances in munition technologies. Merely supplemented T-55s in Soviet service although many were still produced and exported to numerous countries. Fought in many wars, most recently the Syrian Civil war. Currently still in service in a number of countries, many upgraded over the years.

title: b7a_ryuusei
body:
The [b]Aichi B7A Ryūsei[/b] ("Shooting Star") was a carrier-based torpedo and dive bomber operated by the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] during [[World War II]]. It's Allied reporting name was [b]Grace[/b].

The Ryusei entered production late in the war, in May 1944, and only a small number were built. The only two aircraft carriers large enough to operate the Ryusei, [[taihou_(aircraft_carrier)|Taihou]] and [[shinano_(aircraft_carrier)|Shinano]], were sunk before they could embark any of the aircraft. Afterward it was operated from land bases. 

h4. External Links

* "Wikipedia":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aichi_B7A

h4.See also

* [[List of Airplanes]]

title: ryuujou_(aircraft_carrier)
body:
Quoting from Conway (who for whatever reason spelled her name as Ryujo):

"Ryujo, built under the 1927 Programme, was planned with a single hanger, but to double the aircraft complement a second hanger was added without enlarging the ship, which turned out to be lightly built, overloaded and unstable. The flight deck measured 512ft 6in x 75ft 6in. In a reconstruction between 1934 and 1936, the armament was reduced, the hull strengthened and extra bulges added. The forecastle was raised a deck in 1940 to improve seakeeping. Ryujo was by 4 bombs and a torpedo in the Battle of the Eastern Solomons.

title: hms_abercrombie
body: British monitor of the Roberts class. Her turret originated from one of the standby turrets intended for HMS Furious in case her 18in guns were failures. During WWII was twice damaged by moored contact mines, the second time striking 2 of them. Broken up in 1954.

title: ise_(battleship)
body: Lead ship of her class, notable for her mid pair turrets superimposed. Reconstructed during the 1930s similar to the Fusou class. Converted to hybrid battle-carriers after midway due to shortage of carriers in the IJN, losing the rear 2 turrets. Sunk in shallow waters off of Kure by US aircraft and broken up after the war.

title: yamashiro_(battleship)
body: Battleship of the Fuso class. Laid down in November 20, 1913, launched on November 3, 1915, completed on March 31, 1917. Reconstructed during the 1930s with lengthened hull, new machinery, more armor, higher elevation of main armament, and additional AA guns. Sunk at the battle of Surigao Strait from 4 torpedoes and a number of 16in & 14in shell hits.

title: hiei_(battleship)
body: Battlecruiser of the Kongo class. Reconstructed and demilitarized as a training ship between 1929 and 1932. Further reconstructed and remilitarized from 1936-1940 and re-rated as a fast battleship. Her rebuilt fire control arrangements and bridge structure layout served as a model for the Yamato class. Crippled by gunfire at the First Battle of Guadalcanal and sunk by airborne torpedoes.

title: settsu_(battleship)
body: Battleship of the Kawachi class, converted to radio controlled target due to Washington Naval Treaty. BU in 1947. While technically a dreadnought her main armament are in 2 calibers, the end turrets are 50 cal while the wing turrets are 45 cal.

title: soul_edge_(weapon)
body:
[b]Soul Edge[/b] is the central antagonist in the [[soulcalibur|Soul series]] of fighting games and namesake to [[soul edge|the first installment]], a legendary living weapon that seeks to reap souls for power. Originally forged by human hands, at first Soul Edge was just an ordinary sword, but after being bathed in blood and hatred countless times, the sword turned into a demonic weapon and gained a wicked soul called Inferno. Those who grasp its hilt are unable to escape its curse, as its spirit invades the mind like a parasite and drives its wielder insane. As its blade is soaked in blood, it grows in power, yet it manages to shine a polished red. Even when broken into small shards, its influence is still felt. Soul Edge is distinguished by the animate eye and is known to take the form of whatever is most convenient for its wielder.

Soul Edge's most famous owners include the dread pirate [[Cervantes de Leon]], the Azure Knight [[Nightmare (Soulcalibur)|Nightmare]], and [[Pyrrha Alexandra]].

Soul Edge is diametrically opposed by its sibling weapon, [[Soul Calibur (weapon)|Soul Calibur]].

title: harpoon_missile
body:
First introduced in 1977, the Harpoon missile uses active radar homing, and a low-level, sea-skimming cruise trajectory to improve survivability and lethality. It is available in the following versions as listed:

AGM-84: for use on aircraft
RGM-84: for use on naval vessels and coastal batteries; this version has an solid rocket booster that detaches when it is empty
UGM-84: Same as the RGM model but the SRB is encased in a container to allow for use via a submarine's torpedo tubes. This version was retired in 1997.

title: after_burner_(video_game)
body:
アフターバーナー ([i][b]After Burner[/b][/i] or [i][b]AfterBurner[/b][/i]) is a 1987 combat flight simulator arcade [[video game]] by [[Sega]] AM2.

It was one of the first games designed by "Suzuki Yu":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yu_Suzuki. In it the player flies an [[f-14_tomcat|F-14]] [[fighter jet]] using a specialized joystick (with moving seat, in some installations), and the game spawned several home [[game_console|console]] ports ans subsequent sequels.

title: roadhog_(overwatch)
body:
[i]"I'm a one-man apocalypse."[/i]

Real Name: Mako Rutledge
Age: 48
Occupation: Enforcer, Bodyguard
Country: Australia

A tank-class character in [[Overwatch]]. After watching his home become an apocalyptic wasteland, Mako Rutledge donned a mask and took to the broken highways of the Outback on his ramshackle chopper. Little by little, his humanity was forgotten. The last vestiges of Mako faded away and the ruthless killer Roadhog was born. Currently employed as a bodyguard for [[junkrat_(overwatch)|Junkrat]].

h4. Limited event skins

* [[Bajie Roadhog]]
* [[Ice Fisherman Roadhog]]
* [[Junkenstein's Monster]]


h4. External links

* "Overwatch wiki":[http://overwatch.gamepedia.com/Roadhog]

Occupation: Anarchist, Thief, Demolitionist, Mercenary, Scavenger
Country: Australia

A defense-class character in [[Overwatch]]. Junkrat is an explosives-obsessed freak who lives to cause chaos and destruction. He has a low opinion of omnics and those who believe they can be trusted. He likewise has a low opinion of "suits" (corporate businesspersons). After finding a valuable secret in the wasteland of Australia, he turned to a Junker enforcer by the name of [[roadhog_(overwatch)|Roadhog]] for protection in exchange for a 50/50 split of the profits.

title: richelieu_(battleship)
body:
Lead ship of her class, built in response to Italian battleship constructions. Overall design roughly similar to that of Dunkerque class (quadruple main armament turret, main armament all concentrated forward). The only class of French battleship armed with 15in guns...

To quote from Conway

"Richelieu was 95 per cent complete when France surrendered and she proceeded to Dakar, where she was damaged during the British attack. In 1942 she joined the Allies and was sent to the USA for a major refit, emerging in October 1943 with radar added, aircraft and catapults removed, ...

... Richelieu was employed with the British Eastern Fleet in 1944-45 and later off French Indo-China. She paid off in 1959 and was hulked at Brest as an accommodation ship."

title: sovetsky_soyuz
body: Soviet WWII battleship, construction was never finished due to German invasion. [designed] displacement close to that of the Yamato class however main armament (9 x 16in guns) and armor are inferior due to industrial limitations of the USSR.

title: dunkerque
body: Lead ship of her class. Sometimes classified as battlecruisers, initiated the general trend towards fast battleships among European countries. Designed and built as a response to the German pocket battleships, their armor was only designed to resist German 11in guns. Scuttled at Toulon in 1942 when the Germans attempted to seize the Vichy French Fleet.
